sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Browser
    participant Views as views.py
    participant DB as models.py\n(DB)

    User->>Browser: Click "View Notes"
    Browser->>Views: GET /
    Views->>DB: Note.objects.all()
    DB-->>Views: [note1, note2, ...]
    Views-->>Browser: 200 HTML (note_list)
    Browser-->>User: Render list

    %% Create flow (time increases downward)
    User->>Browser: Click "Create Note"
    Browser->>Views: GET /create/
    Views-->>Browser: 200 HTML (note_form)
    User->>Browser: Submit form (POST)
    Browser->>Views: POST /create/ (form data)
    Views->>DB: Note.save()
    DB-->>Views: created note (id)
    Views-->>Browser: Redirect to /
    Browser-->>User: Shows updated list

    %% Detail + Update + Delete (shortened)
    User->>Browser: Click note link
    Browser->>Views: GET /{id}/
    Views->>DB: Note.objects.get(id)
    DB-->>Views: note
    Views-->>Browser: 200 HTML (note_detail)

    User->>Browser: Click "Delete"
    Browser->>Views: POST /delete/{id}/
    Views->>DB: note.delete()
    DB-->>Views: deleted
    Views-->>Browser: Redirect to /
